HLS 26RS-2087 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 45
BY REPRESENTATIVE ZERINGUE
FUNDS/FUNDING: Memorializes Congress to grant an extension of time for expending
American Rescue Plan Act funds in order to complete various critical infrastructure
projects around the state that are integral to the health and safety of Louisiana's
population
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To memorialize the United States Congress to take such actions as are necessary to extend
3 the deadline for expenditure of State and Local Fiscal Recovery Fund dollars
4 received through the American Rescue Plan Act to allow time for completion of
5 critical infrastructure projects integral to the health and safety of Louisiana's
6 population.
7 WHEREAS, Louisiana allocated over seven hundred million dollars of its State and
8 Local Fiscal Recovery Funds received through the American Rescue Plan Act to grant
9 funding for critical water and sewer infrastructure projects around the state; and
10 WHEREAS, these projects span urban and rural areas across the state providing
11 needed repairs, improved access, and upgrades to bring existing systems into regulatory
12 compliance; and
13 WHEREAS, without these grant funds, local communities would have continued to
14 struggle to maintain their existing water and sewer infrastructure, some in such states of
15 disrepair that residents face boil warnings, water outages, brown water, and contaminants;
16 and
17 WHEREAS, Louisiana incorporated robust protocols into its program to guarantee
18 local participation in the project and strict compliance with federal guidelines; however,
19 large-scale infrastructure projects involve complex planning and procurement processes and
20 external complications such as supply chain disruptions and scarcity of qualified engineers
