1 and contractors to perform the labor have made some project completion dates extend
2 beyond the December 31, 2026, deadline for expenditure of these federal dollars; and
3 WHEREAS, without these federal resources, communities around Louisiana will be
4 left with incomplete projects they cannot afford to finish and the health and welfare of
5 Louisiana's citizens will be jeopardized.
6 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
7 memorialize the United States Congress to take such actions as are necessary to extend the
8 deadline for expenditure of State and Local Fiscal Recovery Fund dollars received through
9 the American Rescue Plan Act to allow time for completion of critical infrastructure projects
10 integral to the health and safety of Louisiana's population.
11 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
12 presiding officers of the Senate and the House of Representatives of the Congress of the
13 United States of America and to each member of the Louisiana congressional delegation.
